# Auto Push for Website Updates

- If the user asks to update the website, make changes, or modify site content, treat it as a deploy-intent request by default.
- Complete the full workflow in one run: implement changes, run relevant checks/tests/build, then commit and push to GitHub.
- Use clear commit messages that describe why the update was made.
- If checks fail, fix issues before committing and pushing.
- Only skip push when the user explicitly says not to push or asks for local-only changes.
- Never include secrets in commits; keep deployment credentials in environment variables or secret managers.
